Description: Fragment of neck and sub-round handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp with rose symbol. Clay near fine buff-brown; white inclusions.
Curator's comments: Name Zenodotos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR P.16306.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0927)
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (probably)
